#$ diff -w file1.txt file2.txt

#$ diff -r directory1 directory2

Options:

-u: Use unified format for output (default).
-c: Use context format for output, showing more lines of context around each difference.
-i: Ignore case differences when comparing files.
-w: Ignore all whitespace differences.
-r: Recursively compare directories.
-q: Report only whether files differ, without details.
-B: Ignore changes that just insert or delete blank lines.
















